en_4497781_0	President Maithripala Sirisena says that the country will not sign any agreement which is deemed a threat to domestic entrepreneurs. The President made this statement at a special meeting organised by committee members of Sri Lankan Youth Entrepreneurs in Battaramulla.
en_4497781_1	The meeting provided an opportunity to table issues and challenges faced by Sri Lankan entrepreneurs. Speaking at the meeting, the President noted that the previous regime issued 16 licenses to international companies to engage in gem-mining.
en_4497781_2	He stated that as soon as he took over the Ministry of Environment he annulled all these licenses.
en_4497781_3	The President went onto note that if these institutions are run in a correct manner and with the the income that flows to the government we will be able close the gap of our national income.
